      <%# Section 1 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">1. Purpose of the Document</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued">The purpose and objective of this policy is to give effect to the provisions of the Protection of Personal Information Act to safeguard Personal Information. It gives effect to our commitment to protecting Personal Information obtained from Data Subjects in compliance with the POPI Act.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 2 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">2. Application of This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">POPI Act gives effect to the constitutional right to privacy, regulates the manner in which Personal Information may be Processed, and provides rights and remedies to protect Personal Information.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">POPI Act applies to Processing of Personal Information in any form by a Responsible Party who is domiciled in South Africa or if not domiciled in South Africa, makes use of automated or non-automated means, unless the Processing relates only to the forwarding of Personal Information.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">The main rationale of POPI Act is to promote the protection of Personal Information and to bring South Africa's privacy laws in line with international standards. It limits the rights of businesses and public bodies to collect, Process, store, and share Personal Information and to only do so in line with the law.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Chancen SA has a legal duty to ensure that all Personal Information it Processes is lawfully Processed in terms of the POPI Act.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">This policy must be read alongside the following governing documents:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Chancen IT Policy</li>
          <li>Safeguarding Policy</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-subdued">This policy shall be revised annually by the Compliance Department, reviewed by the Country Director and approved by the Executive Team.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 3 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">3. Definitions</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-4">For purposes of this policy, the below mentioned words and/or phrases shall have the following meaning assigned to them:</p>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-subdued">
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Competent Person"</strong> means any person who is legally competent to consent to any action or decision being taken in respect of any matter concerning a Minor.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Consent"</strong> means any voluntary, specific and informed expression of will in terms of which permission is given for the processing of Personal Information.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Constitution"</strong> means the Constitution of the Republic of South Africa, 1996.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Data Subject"</strong> means the person to whom Personal Information relates and for purposes of this policy includes, but is not limited to, Chancen SA's governance and/or appointed officer-bearers, prospective members, members, employees, partner organisations, subsidiaries, donors and funders, visitors, contractors, service providers, agents, members of the public.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"De-identify"</strong> means to delete any information that identifies the Data Subject, can be used or manipulated by a reasonably foreseeable method to identify the Data Subject, or can be linked by a reasonably foreseeable method to other information that identifies the Data Subject.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Information Officer"</strong> means a person appointed by Chancen SA as required in terms of section 55 of the POPIA.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Deputy Information Officer"</strong> means a person appointed by Chancen SA as required in terms of section 56 of POPIA.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Intermediaries"</strong> means any person rendering services as an intermediary.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Minor"</strong> means a natural person under the age of 18 years who is not legally competent, without the assistance of a competent person, to take any action or decision in respect of any matter concerning him or herself.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Personal Information"</strong> means information relating to an identifiable, living, natural person, and where it is applicable, an identifiable, existing juristic person, including but not limited to: information relating to race, gender, sex, pregnancy, marital status, national, ethnic or social origin, colour, sexual orientation, age, physical or mental health, well-being, disability, religion, conscience, belief, culture, language and birth; education, medical, financial, criminal or employment history; identifying numbers, symbols, email addresses, telephone numbers, location information, online identifiers; biometric information; personal opinions, views or preferences; private correspondence; and the name of the person where it appears alongside other Personal Information.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"POPI Act"</strong> stands for Protection of Personal Information Act, 4 of 2013.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Privacy Notice"</strong> is a notice that describes how Personal Information is used by Chancen SA as a result of a Data Subject's engagement with Chancen SA.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Processing"</strong> means any operation or activity or any set of operations, whether or not by automatic means, concerning Personal Information, including the collection, receipt, recording, organisation, collation, storage, updating or modification, retrieval, alteration, consultation or use; dissemination by means of transmission, distribution or making available in any other form; or merging, linking, restriction, degradation, erasure or destruction of information.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Regulator"</strong> means the Information Regulator as established by section 39 of POPI Act.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Responsible Party"</strong> means a member of the public or private body or any other persons which alone or in conjunction with others, determines the purpose of and means for Processing Personal Information.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-primary">"Third Parties"</strong> means Intermediaries, binder holders, companies in our group of companies, contractors and verification agencies.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <%# Section 4 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">4. Forms, Documents, Policies</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">This policy must be read together with the following related documents:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li><strong>IT Policy</strong> — focuses on information management and security covering the people, processes and technologies at Chancen International.</li>
          <li><strong>Safeguarding Policy</strong> — looks at the protection of people, particularly young adults, vulnerable adults, Chancen beneficiaries or children who are among Chancen community members from any harm.</li>
          <li><strong>PAIA Manual</strong> — guides members of the public, Chancen Members, prospective members and Chancen Staff on procedures to follow when requesting personal information from Chancen South Africa.</li>
          <li><strong>Non Disclosure Agreement</strong> — outlines the requirements of service providers to hold Chancen information with confidentiality.</li>
          <li><strong>Employment Contract</strong> — Chancen SA contract of employment outlining the requirements for confidentiality from staff members.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 5 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">5. Processing Personal Information</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">POPI Act sets out the following conditions for the lawful Processing of Personal Information:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Duty by a public body;</li>
          <li>Legal obligation to perform the Processing of Personal Information;</li>
          <li><strong>Processing limitation</strong> — Personal Information may only be Processed if it is adequate, relevant and not excessive given the purpose for which it is collected;</li>
          <li><strong>Purpose specification</strong> — Personal Information must be collected for a specific, explicitly defined and lawful purpose related to the activity of the Responsible Party;</li>
          <li><strong>Further Processing limitation</strong> — where Personal Information is received from a Third Party and passed on to the Responsible Party for further Processing, the further Processing must be compatible with the purpose for which it was initially processed;</li>
          <li><strong>Personal Information quality</strong> — Personal Information must be complete, accurate, not misleading and updated where necessary;</li>
          <li><strong>Openness</strong> — the Data Subject must be informed when collecting information and the specific nature thereof;</li>
          <li><strong>Security safeguards</strong> — the Responsible Party must ensure the integrity of the Personal Information by taking measures to prevent the loss, damage or unauthorised destruction of the Personal Information; and</li>
          <li><strong>Data Subject specification</strong> — the Data Subject has the right to request a Responsible Party to confirm, free of charge, whether they hold Personal Information about them.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Chancen SA is required to Process Personal Information to enter into contracts, to fulfil contractual requirements and to fulfil its regulatory obligation. Chancen SA further Processes Personal Information to enable it to enhance the experience of the Data Subject in relation to the business relationship. To ensure that Data Subject is always treated fairly and in promoting transparency, Chancen SA will disclose up-front the purpose of Processing the Personal Information obtained and what it may further be used for.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Where Personal Information may potentially be used for other objectives than originally acquired for, Chancen SA will, prior to Processing the Personal Information, obtain Consent from the Data Subject concerned. Chancen SA may however Process Personal Information in absence of a Consent if Processing is required to comply with the law or for protecting the Data Subject's legitimate interests.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued">Chancen SA will not transfer Personal Information to any entity outside of South Africa unless such transfer complies with Section 72 of the POPI Act. This includes ensuring that the recipient is subject to laws, binding corporate rules, or agreements that provide an adequate level of data protection. Data Subjects will be informed prior to any such transfer.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 6 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">6. Collection of Personal Information</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li>Chancen SA will notify the Regulator of its intention to process personal information.</li>
          <li>Chancen SA will inform the Data Subject that his or her personal information will be collected and it is included in our agreements with our members.</li>
          <li>Chancen SA will give the Data Subject information on its name, address, and the purpose for which the personal information is being collected.</li>
          <li>Chancen SA will primarily collect Personal Information directly from the Data Subject, which would typically be face-to-face or via other channels like emails, telephone, social media and website.</li>
          <li>Chancen SA will take steps to ensure that collected data is complete, accurate, not misleading and up to date, including encouraging data subjects to capture their data accurately and seeking consent to verify their Personal Information through authorised third parties.</li>
          <li>Verify Personal Information accuracy through credit bureaus.</li>
          <li>Personal Information may also be collected from Third Parties; however, the Data Subject's Consent will be requested prior to obtaining Personal Information from Third Parties.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 7 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">7. Disclosure of Personal Information</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li>Chancen SA may share any Personal Information of a Data Subject with a Third Party contracted to perform services approved by Chancen SA in terms of contractual agreement. In such instances, Chancen SA will ensure that Third Parties have the relevant controls in place to comply with the conditions for lawful Processing of Personal Information in terms of the POPI Act.</li>
          <li>All requests for Personal Information will be handled by the Information Officer and the Deputy Information Officer.</li>
          <li>Chancen SA may also disclose any Personal Information when it has a duty or right to do so in terms of applicable laws or in legal proceedings.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 8 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">8. Protection of Personal Information</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">In terms of section 19 of POPI Act, a Responsible Party must ensure the integrity and confidentiality of Personal Information in its possession or under its control by taking appropriate, reasonable technical and organisational measures to prevent loss of, damage to or unauthorised destruction of Personal Information, unlawful access to or Processing of Personal Information.</p>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">POPI Act requires that Personal Information should be adequately protected to avoid unauthorised access. The following security controls are in place to protect Personal Information:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li>Personal Information is treated as confidential and not disclosed unless required by law;</li>
          <li>High level information technology controls are in place to maintain the protection of Personal Information;</li>
          <li>High level anti-virus programs;</li>
          <li>Access rights in place;</li>
          <li>Computer passwords in place;</li>
          <li>Assessment of data quality controls in place to ensure the accuracy and completeness of Personal Information;</li>
          <li>A third party service provider is mandated to ensure safeguarding of Personal Information;</li>
          <li>Personal Information is stored at a third-party service provider who is subject to POPI Act;</li>
          <li>Employees, members and service providers of Chancen SA sign Non Disclosure Agreements as part of the employment contract and/or service level agreement;</li>
          <li>Hardcopy files are archived at a secured place.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 9 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">9. Cybersecurity and Information Technology Safeguards</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Chancen SA is committed to protecting all Personal Information through practical and effective cybersecurity measures. This ensures that personal information remains confidential, accurate, and available only to authorized staff.</p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">9.1 Governance</h3>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Chancen SA maintains a cybersecurity framework to identify risks, apply appropriate security measures, and regularly check that they are working.</p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">9.2 Access and Device Security</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Only authorized staff may access personal information based on their role.</li>
          <li>Strong passwords, multi-factor authentication, and secure device settings are required.</li>
          <li>Laptops, phones, and other devices storing personal information must be protected and not shared.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">9.3 Data Handling and Transmission</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Personal information should be encrypted when sent electronically.</li>
          <li>Staff must avoid suspicious emails, links, or requests for information.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">9.4 Monitoring and Incident Response</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Critical systems and personal information are backed up regularly.</li>
          <li>Backups are encrypted and stored securely.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">9.5 Incident Reporting</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>Any suspected breach, lost device, or unauthorized access must be reported immediately to the Information Officer or IT team.</li>
          <li>Affected Data Subjects and regulators will be notified if required by law.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">9.6 Third-Party Services</h3>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Any external service handling personal information must meet our security standards and have signed agreements to protect data.</p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">9.7 Training and Awareness</h3>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">All staff will receive regular cybersecurity training to understand threats and their responsibilities under POPIA.</p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-primary mb-2">9.8 Continuous Improvement</h3>
        <p class="text-subdued">Our cybersecurity measures are reviewed regularly and updated when laws, technology, or risks change.</p>
      </section>

      <%# Section 11 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">11. Retention and Deleting of Personal Information</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">Chancen SA will retain Personal Information only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purpose for which the information was collected, or as required by applicable laws. This includes recordkeeping obligations under tax, credit or employment legislation. Retention may also be justified when:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1 mb-3">
          <li>The retention of such record is required by law;</li>
          <li>Chancen SA requires such record for lawful purposes related to its function or activities (ongoing business purposes);</li>
          <li>The retention of such record is required in terms of a contractual agreement between the parties thereto; or</li>
          <li>The necessary Consent has been obtained from the Data Subject and is for a legitimate interest.</li>
          <li>Chancen SA will de-identify, destroy or delete a record of Personal Information as soon as reasonably practicable, where it is no longer authorised to retain such record.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">In the event that Chancen SA has reasonable grounds to believe that a Data Subject's Personal Information has been accessed or acquired by an unauthorized party, the following steps will be taken:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li>Contain the incident and mitigate any immediate risk to affected parties.</li>
          <li>Notify the Information Regulator as soon as reasonably possible, as required under Section 22 of the POPI Act.</li>
          <li>Notify the affected Data Subject(s) in writing, including details of the breach, the nature of the data involved, and mitigation steps taken.</li>
          <li>Log the incident and conduct an internal investigation to determine root cause and corrective action.</li>
          <li>Review and strengthen safeguards to prevent future occurrences.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 12 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">12. The Rights of a Data Subject</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued mb-3">The Data Subject has the right to lawful Processing of their Personal Information in terms of the provisions of POPI Act, including the right to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-5 text-subdued space-y-1">
          <li>Be made aware when Personal Information is collected, accessed or acquired by an unauthorized person;</li>
          <li>Inquire whether Chancen SA holds Personal Information of the Data Subject and to request access to the Personal Information;</li>
          <li>Withdraw Consent, provided that the lawfulness of the Processing of Personal Information before such withdrawal or the Processing of Personal Information required to exercise legitimate obligation as provided by POPI Act will not be affected;</li>
          <li>Request, where necessary, the correction, destruction or deletion of Personal Information;</li>
          <li>Object on reasonable grounds relating to a particular situation to the Processing of Personal Information;</li>
          <li>Object to the processing of Personal Information at any time for purposes of direct marketing or unsolicited electronic communications;</li>
          <li>Not to have Personal Information Processed for purposes of direct marketing by means of unsolicited electronic communications;</li>
          <li>Submit a complaint to the Regulator regarding the alleged interference with the protection of the Personal Information of any Data Subject;</li>
          <li>Institute a civil action for damages against Chancen SA in a court with competent jurisdiction, for breach of any of the provisions of POPI Act;</li>
          <li>Not to be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing of Personal Information, including profiling, where such processing leads to legal or significant effects — unless the decision is necessary for contract performance, authorized by law with safeguards, or based on the Data Subject's explicit consent, in which case Chancen SA will provide the opportunity to make representations, explain the logic of the decision in plain language, and offer a human review upon request.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <%# Section 13 %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-3">13. Limitation</h2>
        <p class="text-subdued">Chancen SA Processes Personal Information of Minors to the extent allowed to fulfil its contractual obligation and where there is a legal obligation to disclose that Personal Information. Chancen SA does not directly engage or enter into contract with a Minor without the Consent of a Competent Person.</p>
      </section>

